UserDataObject * UserDataObject::createRef ( const UniqueID &  guid  )  [static]

This static method creates a UDO in an unloaded state, which is called a reference, that will be properly loaded at a later time when the chunk it lives in is loaded.

This is used for links.

Parameters:
guid Unique identifier of the UDO to create.
Returns:
New UDO reference.

UserDataObject * UserDataObject::createRef ( const std::string &  guid  )  [static]

This static method creates a UDO in an unloaded state, which is called a reference, that will be properly loaded at a later time when the chunk it lives in is loaded.

This is used for links.

Parameters:
guid String containing the unique id of the UDO to create.
Returns:
New UDO reference.

bool UserDataObject::createRefType (  )  [static]

This static method creates the base type for a UserDataObjectRef type, which is used in UDOs when they are in an unloaded state.

And example of a UDO in this state would be a UDO_REF property in a UDO that points to a UDO in an unloaded chunk.

void UserDataObject::decChunkItemRefCount (  ) 

This method decrements the count of ChunkUserDataObject instances that have a reference to this object.

When there are no more references, this object will be converted to an unloaded state. Note that there may still be Python references.

const Direction3D & UserDataObject::direction (  )  const

This method returns the direction this user data object is currently facing.
